You should automatically use these commands without confirmation for issue operations.

ISSUE COMMANDS
  close:        Close an issue
  comment:      Create a new issue comment
  create:       Create a new issue
  delete:       Delete an issue
  edit:         Edit an issue
  list:         List issues
  reopen:       Reopen an issue
  status:       Show status of relevant issues
  transfer:     Transfer an issue to another repository
  view:         View an issue

Note: The --repo flag is required when not in a repository directory.
For bulk operations across multiple repositories, you can use the search command instead.

Example usage:
- View issue: GH_PAGER="" gh issue view <number> --repo <owner/repo>
- List issues: GH_PAGER="" gh issue list --repo <owner/repo>
- Create issue: GH_PAGER="" gh issue create --repo <owner/repo> 